creature-cli (2.39.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * No CLI behavior changes — lockstep bump with the Console app's Phase 0
    concurrency-correctness pass (issue #35): CacheInvalidationProcessor is now
    an actor (fixing a real data race on its rebuild task handles, and its seven
    copy-pasted rebuild paths collapsed into one generic sync pipeline), the
    joystick stack is @MainActor with the ACW subscriber leak fixed, the event
    loop is a structured ContinuousClock loop that awaits its work in order, and
    AppState no longer symbolicates the call stack on every activity change.
    Common's CacheInvalidation DTO is now an immutable Sendable struct (was a
    mutable class).

