creature-cli (2.25.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Websocket message handling is now an ordered ingestion pipeline: incoming
    messages are processed strictly in arrival order through a single consumer
    task instead of racing fire-and-forget Tasks. MessageProcessor protocol
    methods are now async.
  * On Linux, websocket text frames are yielded synchronously from the NIO
    event loop, fixing a frame reordering race in the NIO client.
  * Snapshot-style state streams now use bufferingNewest(1) so slow consumers
    skip to the freshest state instead of replaying a stale backlog.
  * creature-cli + creature-mqtt + creature-agent: versions synced to 2.25.4
    (creature-mqtt was 2.20.1, creature-agent was 2.23.0).

